data.description: OPEN HOUSE SUN 10/22 FROM 1-4 !  RARE FIND AND GREAT PRICE!  Welcome to this exquisite Spanish-style home nestled in the prestigious, gated Presidio neighborhood.   The home's exterior showcases a durable terracotta tile roof with a recently painted stucco facade.  McMillan Homes is a very energy efficient builder!  NO CARPET - only tile and warm hardwood floors lead you past the dining space to the heart of the home.  The gourmet area is sure to impress with its espresso-colored cabinetry accentuated with miles of granite counters and stainless-steel appliances. Accent wall in family room provides an elegant backdrop for all your entertainment electronics or large display cases.  The large primary suite provides a view of the treetops while being on the main floor and an ensuite bathroom looks like new with a spacious closet with built-in's.  Upstairs boasts a game and study area and three bedrooms with two bathrooms.  HUGE BONUS FEATURE - follow the steps down to a FULL LOWER LEVEL with spacious third living area and full bedroom and bath.  This space is perfect for older children, guests or could be a primary suite if the main level primary is needed for an older generation family member.  Could be an amazing media room, completely separate office area, storage, gym or craft room, etc.  SO MUCH FLEXIBILITY!  Enjoy TWO outdoor patio areas - a covered & extended patio from the lower level and an upper patio from the main level.  Great entertaining options for both!  Soak up the privacy and beauty from more than 10 mature fruit trees planted along the fence line in the ample backyard.  Don't miss the vegetable garden on the side of the backyard.  Walk to a highly-rated private school.  This coveted north-central location places you minutes away from major employers & attractions such as USAA, Valero, UTSA, Fiesta Texas, La Cantera, and The Rim.  The community is highly sought after for its convenience to Loop 1604 and the amenities are among the best. Bike to Dwight D. Eisenhower park in minutes!  The park is popular for hiking with over 5 miles of picturesque trails. There are also picnic areas, a playground, camp sites and the Howard W. Peak trail over IH-10 to La Cantera and beyond.
